test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x78b40636ab40>([-87])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x78b40636ab40> = [[1, -87], [1, -87, 1], [1, -87, 1, -87], [-87], [-87, 1], [-87, 1, -87], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x78b40636ab40>([1, -87])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x78b40636ab40> = [[1, -87], [1, -87, 1], [1, -87, 1, -87], [-87], [-87, 1], [-87, 1, -87], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x78b40636ab40>([-87, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x78b40636ab40> = [[1, -87], [1, -87, 1], [1, -87, 1, -87], [-87], [-87, 1], [-87, 1, -87], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert -261 == -87
 +  where -261 = <built-in function prod>([-87, -1, -3])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
